qS5oGwFEvr8m38oTE7gSys6dqTHOmKN07D-ABr_Jkcjfu05J56fLqo-NjUvc7X01ZBtfK259Mitbvj1DUxeZgf_Rg8Dh69DTf1vfK0KL311_mQRmXK3Xk3QwdNYkTYKifTJO4Ak8OX_ECW62J4mqBMoIGVJwpPc0M1xKoctbwmJQ9G2chjlgGPDZyK_2-gdq4LGPuKo4DiFPKOOwWNGC3ubdcgQPvdldmcR3YGPpKHBbIZL8cTgBQnlTcDU8DhwT2lqUBB4Cuum8ToIIOkvPki2CWbtV_q5BuI6e_XL2eA9YG8epZeO9HUL6tvJHXwOq6GaFo1xxAVN160_dVHhnMD8Jb1qa3Pla4T8L-xQFJapdCchvTuWTdyxeGaoWD1OCtF1EZtzLetZ6L0Z5exy-lPfuqhnrG1Bm6WypYuUDaJRK_LCAXsC55qG6RQnDseRhAnqzm3241qN3o8bYQ_1bdsS35pBEdW21TiayGZKVEKbA1EfTGIIn7El7DeE67EcyQXsc4wmdjcRLyh6r3mHapYirvLFYGfMikDTb53_t6XiiB_ELLd6lbdc0Q0ACFBFg0ieUkEOw-cOaWsR86_Jkg8VHFPgQobkeQP-eiI_89LTqJHnsTGe1bjhWli2fDXKAjSs_WHM_TYWJZe4vTu36kPU2O_D1LSYu69IXntoM3kckL6nd7ndzk44SggrfZOkiIA2aKOSYDVoujwJIpDAzMsMmLeo45Y6z69Ah1LjP-HhRPet9kgi5pX-A9PGrAuhGmrsLjqqtacuPIOSFxDIjdbY7rNf62xI29q88dUyFpE8FKv7i_EveVYNG2lJ9Zdrr_0DFtA-6yN1CUhdRFw=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test accessibility**\\n\\nI’m thinking about whether all the top-level test classes should be public. It makes sense in terms of accessibility, but then I wonder if a helper should also remain at the top level. Is there a benefit to keeping certain tests private? What about organization and encapsulation? Balancing accessibility and good structure is essential here. I have to weigh how this affects both usability and maintainability of the tests. Let's explore these aspects further!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Checking context details**\\n\\nI noticed there's no actual class named DefaultCamelContext, but that's fine. I need to focus on calls to loadResourcesAsURL next. Specifically, at line 685, we've got loader.getResources(uri). If it returns a non-null value, it should return as expected. It's essential to verify this to ensure everything runs smoothly. Let's keep an eye on these details for consistency!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class naming conventions**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the class name for `ObjectHelper.loadClass` and how it uses a nested class name that includes a $. The source code mentions replacing $ when naming tests for inner classes, but that might not apply here. The Native Image metadata seems acceptable as is. If I want to avoid using $, can I just refer to `ObjectHelperTest.class` instead? Also, I should check if the test class is public and has a no-arg constructor, and whether it defaults to a package.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_rXb42hqyOlwMQbnPztQzwgAK|fc_0d96a10243801e210169f796af42e08194a9f8b0ee2f556bbb", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.camel/camel-util/4.19.0/src/test/java/org_apache_camel/camel_util/ObjectHelperTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_apache_camel.camel_util;\n\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.util.Enumeration;\n\nimport org.apache.camel.util.ObjectHelper;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class ObjectHelperTest {\n    private static final String DEFAULT_CAMEL_CONTEXT_CLASS = \"org.apache.camel.impl.DefaultCamelContext\";\n    private static final String MISSING_RESOURCE_NAME = \"missing-camel-util-resource-for-object-helper-test.txt\";\n\n    @Test\n    void loadsApplicationClassArrayByName() {\n        Class<?> loadedType = ObjectHelper.loadClass(ObjectHelperTest.class.getName() + \"[]\",\n                ObjectHelperTest.class.getClassLoader(), false);\n\n        assertThat(loadedType).isEqualTo(ObjectHelperTest[].class);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void detectsPublicAndNonPrivateNoArgConstructors() {\n        assertThat(ObjectHelper.hasDefaultPublicNoArgConstructor(PublicNoArgConstructorCandidate.class)).isTrue();\n        assertThat(ObjectHelper.hasDefaultNoArgConstructor(PackageNoArgConstructorCandidate.class)).isTrue();\n        assertThat(ObjectHelper.hasDefaultNoArgConstructor(PrivateNoArgConstructorCandidate.class)).isFalse();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void looksUpPublicStaticConstantFieldValues() {\n        assertThat(ObjectHelper.lookupConstantFieldValue(ConstantHolder.class, \".TEXT\")).isEqualTo(\"camel-util\");\n        assertThat(ObjectHelper.lookupConstantFieldValue(ConstantHolder.class, \"NUMBER\")).isEqualTo(\"19\");\n        assertThat(ObjectHelper.lookupConstantFieldValue(ConstantHolder.class, \"MISSING\")).isNull();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void probesAllResourceUrlLoadersBeforeReturningNull() {\n        ClassLoader originalContextClassLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n        try {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(new MissingResourceCamelContextClassLoader());\n\n            URL resource = ObjectHelper.loadResourceAsURL(MISSING_RESOURCE_NAME, new MissingResourceClassLoader());\n\n            assertThat(resource).isNull();\n        } finally {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(originalContextClassLoader);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void probesCamelContextClassLoaderWhenLoadingResourceEnumerations() {\n        ClassLoader originalContextClassLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n        try {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(new ThrowingResourcesCamelContextClassLoader());\n\n            Enumeration<URL> resources = ObjectHelper.loadResourcesAsURL(MISSING_RESOURCE_NAME,\n                    new ThrowingResourcesClassLoader());\n\n            assertThat(resources).isNotNull();\n            assertThat(resources.hasMoreElements()).isFalse();\n        } finally {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(originalContextClassLoader);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void fallsBackToObjectHelperClassLoaderWhenResourceEnumerationLookupFails() {\n        ClassLoader originalContextClassLoader = Threa